 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Program Manager, Digital Pathology & AI Reveal Biosciences San Diego, CA 92121 Remote Full-time Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Reveal Biosciences has developed a new generation of data powered pathology to enhance research and improve global healthcare. Our proprietary AI powered platform, imageDx, delivers scientists and pathologists a novel class of actionable, quantitative data to accelerate research and enhance patient care. Reveal was recently acquired by CellCarta, a global precision medicine company with strong expertise in clinical trials. 
We are seeking a talented Program Manager to lead the integration and validation of imageDx AI-powered digital assays throughout CellCarta to support global research and clinical trials. In this role, you will: 
Work closely with the Reveal and CellCarta teams to develop a plan and prioritize the validation of existing AI digital assays within CellCarta facilities globally. 
Identify high value opportunities to expand the imageDx digital assay portfolio. Collaborate with data scientists, pathologists, and researchers to manage the development and deployment of new digital assays targeting pharma clients. 
Initiate pivotal studies, ideally with pharma collaboration, for publication and market awareness. 
Establish credibility-building networks with KOL at pharma and academic venues. 
Promote the company’s AI vision and present business capabilities to clients. 
The successful candidate will have: 
An Advanced Degree in Life Sciences, Pathology, or a related field, PhD or MD preferred 
Experience in digital pathology and an understanding of clinical validation requirements 
Strategic thinker with exceptional communication and presentation skills 
Reveal offers a competitive salary and benefits package: 
Work remotely or from our headquarters in San Diego 
An open, collaborative and engaged team focused on making a difference 
Flexible work schedule with the ability to work remotely 
4 weeks paid leave per year with extended holidays 
Team Building events including company lunches and outings 
Healthcare plans including medical (HMO & PPO), vision, and dental 
Employer paid life insurance 
